text.tspan: H & M claims will be handled directly by Technical department.8.8RECORD KEEPINGThe cases, both current and closed, will be filed in the respective ship’s cupboard. New file reference number for each case should be allocated. The new file reference number can be vessel's 3 Letter code, followedby year, then by number (e.g. SPH/10/001). 8.9CHANGE OF VESSEL PARTICULARRequest for new insurance policy (P&I & H+M) and Bunker CLC whenever there is a change in the vessel’s and registered owner’sparticulars.9TAKE OVER AND HAND OVER OF VESSELS9.1TAKING OVER A VESSEL UNDER MANAGEMENTWhen taking over a vessel under management, the process appended below is to be complied with and the vessel shall not departport unless it has been verified and documented that vessel is adequately manned, certified and stored and that staff have beenfamiliarized and have had adequate rest.9.2VESSEL HANDOVERWhen handing over a vessel under management, the process / checks to be carried out are outlined in "TA -10 - Vessel HandoverChecklist".
